# FFJORD(model, p, st, re, basedist, tspan, args, kwargs)

function FFJORD(model, tspan, args...; p::P=nothing, st=nothing, basedist::D=nothing, kwargs...) where , Nothing}, RE <: Function, D <: Union} _p, re = Flux.destructure(model) if isnothing(p) p = _p end if isnothing(basedist) size_input = size(model[1].weight, 2) type_input = eltype(model[1].weight) basedist = MvNormal(zeros(type_input, size_input), Diagonal(ones(type_input, size_input))) end FFJORD(model, p, st, re, basedist, tspan, args, kwargs) end
When running on GPU e needs to be passed separately
# ffjord_(u, p, t) = ffjord(u, p, t, n.re, e; regularize, monte_carlo)
